{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842540907,"sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","part":{"id":"prt_d7876ae20001E709XVLJDqxZ2w","messageID":"msg_d7876a14a0010Zu3MolKqd0S3U","sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ba95e8a6d6704479965d14fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-005\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: TBD\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n18: \n19: ### AR-005-001: TBD\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** \n22: - **WHEN** \n23: - **THEN** \n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scenario: Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n28: \n29: ### AR-005-010: TBD\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN**\n32: - **WHEN**\n33: - **THEN**\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n40: - Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-005\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: TBD\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n\n### AR-005-001: TBD\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775842540881,"end":1775842540906}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842540910,"sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","part":{"id":"prt_d7876b819001YgF2I2yBXy8WTo","messageID":"msg_d7876a14a0010Zu3MolKqd0S3U","sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a1cf2c672ccb48409ca19fa9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-004\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (clientset, informers, listers)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n18: \n19: ### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n24: - **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address via `--port` flag (default 8080)\n25: - **AND** SHALL support graceful shutdown within 30 seconds\n26: \n27: ### AR-004-002: Health check endpoints\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n30: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/healthz`\n31: - **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with status \"ok\"\n32: - **AND** SHALL return Content-Type `text/plain`\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** HTTP server running on configured port\n35: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/readyz`\n36: - - **THEN** it SHALL return HTTP 200 OK when server is ready to serve traffic\n37: - **AND** it SHALL return HTTP 503 Service Unavailable when not ready\n38: \n39: ### AR-004-003: Server configuration via flags\n40: \n41: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary with flag parsing\n42: - **WHEN** started with `--port=9090`\n43: - **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL listen on port 9090\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary\n46: - **WHEN** started with no flags\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL use default port 8080\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Scenario: Kubernetes Client Integration\n52: \n53: ### AR-004-010: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at default location (`~/.kube/config`)\n56: - **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `client.NewForConfig`\n57: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n58: - **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n59: \n60: ### AR-004-011: Client initialization in-cluster\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes pod with ServiceAccount mounted\n63: - **WHEN** creating Kubernetes client via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Clientset with credentials from the ServiceAccount\n65: - **AND** SHALL be able to communicate with the Kubernetes API server\n66: \n67: ### AR-004-012: Client resource cleanup\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes Clientset is created\n70: - **WHEN** the server shuts down gracefully\n71: - **THEN** all HTTP clients SHALL be properly closed\n72: - **AND** SHALL not leak goroutines or connections\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD API\n77: \n78: ### AR-004-020: Create AgentRuntime\n79: \n80: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with AgentRuntime CRD\n81: - **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with valid AgentRuntime JSON body\n82: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n83: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n86: - **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid AgentRuntime JSON\n87: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n90: - **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n92: \n93: ### AR-004-021: Get AgentRuntime\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n96: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n97: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime resource as JSON\n98: - **AND** the response SHALL include the complete resource with metadata and spec\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n101: - **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n102: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n103: \n104: ### AR-004-022: List AgentRuntimes\n105: \n106: - **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n107: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n108: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with an AgentRuntimeList containing all matching resources\n109: - **AND** SHALL support `labelSelector` query parameter for filtering\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n112: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to non-existent namespace\n113: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n114: \n115: ### AR-004-023: Update AgentRuntime\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n118: - **WHEN** client sends PUT request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated AgentRuntime JSON\n119: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the AgentRuntime resource in Kubernetes\n120: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n121: \n122: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n123: - **WHEN** client sends PUT request with mismatched name in body and URL\n124: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n125: \n126: ### AR-004-024: Delete AgentRuntime\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-runtime\" in namespace \"default\"\n129: - **WHEN** client sends DELETE request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n130: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the AgentRuntime resource from Kubernetes\n131: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n134: - **WHEN** client sends DELETE request for non-existent AgentRuntime\n135: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n136: \n137: ### AR-004-025: Get AgentRuntime status\n138: \n139: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with status field populated\n140: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n141: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime status\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n144: - **WHEN** client sends GET request for status subresource of non-existent AgentRuntime\n145: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n146: \n147: ### AR-004-026: Patch AgentRuntime status\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime\n150: - **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with JSON Patch\n151: - **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field of the AgentRuntime\n152: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n153: \n154: ### AR-004-027: Watch AgentRuntimes\n155: \n156: - **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist\n157: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n158: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n159: - **AND** SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON)\n160: - **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as resources change\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD API\n165: \n166: ### AR-004-030: Create CodeInterpreter\n167: \n168: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with Kubernetes client connected to a cluster with CodeInterpreter CRD\n169: - **WHEN** client sends POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with valid CodeInterpreter JSON body\n170: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n171: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with the created resource in response body\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n174: - **WHEN** client sends POST request with invalid CodeInterpreter JSON\n175: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with error details\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n178: - **WHEN** client sends POST request to non-existent namespace\n179: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n180: \n181: ### AR-004-031: Get CodeInterpreter\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-interpreter\" in namespace \"default\"\n184: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n185: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter resource as JSON\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n188: - **WHEN** client sends GET request for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n189: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n190: \n191: ### AR-004-032: List CodeInterpreters\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace \"default\"\n194: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n195: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with a CodeInterpreterList containing all matching resources\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n198: - **WHEN** client sends GET request with `labelSelector` query parameter\n199: - **THEN** the server SHALL filter results by the specified label selector\n200: \n201: ### AR-004-033: Update CodeInterpreter\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n204: - **WHEN** client sends PUT request with updated CodeInterpreter JSON\n205: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the CodeInterpreter resource in Kubernetes\n206: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the updated resource\n207: \n208: ### AR-004-034: Delete CodeInterpreter\n209: \n210: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n211: - **WHEN** client sends DELETE request\n212: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the CodeInterpreter resource\n213: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the deleted resource\n214: \n215: ### AR-004-035: Get CodeInterpreter status\n216: \n217: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with status field populated\n218: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`\n219: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the CodeInterpreter status\n220: \n221: ### AR-004-036: Patch CodeInterpreter status\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n224: - **WHEN** client sends PATCH request to status subresource\n225: - **THEN** the server SHALL patch only the status field\n226: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with the patched resource\n227: \n228: ### AR-004-037: Watch CodeInterpreters\n229: \n230: - **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist\n231: - **WHEN** client sends GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n232: - **THEN** the server SHALL stream WATCH_EVENT objects as NDJSON\n233: - **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ## Scenario: Middleware & Observability\n238: \n239: ### AR-004-040: Request logging middleware\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** HTTP server with logging middleware configured\n242: - **WHEN** any HTTP request is received\n243: - **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and latency\n244: - **AND** SHALL log at appropriate level (info for success, error for 5xx)\n245: \n246: ### AR-004-041: Metrics collection\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** HTTP server with metrics middleware\n249: - **WHEN** HTTP requests are processed\n250: - **THEN** the server SHALL track request count by method and path\n251: - **AND** SHALL track request duration histogram\n252: - **AND** SHALL track response status code distribution\n253: \n254: ### AR-004-042: Error handling middleware\n255: \n256: - **GIVEN** HTTP server with error handling middleware\n257: - **WHEN** a handler returns an error\n258: - **THEN** the server SHALL map Kubernetes API errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n259: - **AND** SHALL return structured error response with message and details\n260: - **AND** SHALL log the error with appropriate context\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Scenario: API Format & Compatibility\n265: \n266: ### AR-004-050: JSON content type\n267: \n268: - **GIVEN** HTTP server\n269: - **WHEN** client sends request with `Accept: application/json`\n270: - **THEN** the server SHALL return responses with `Content-Type: application/json`\n271: \n272: - **GIVEN** HTTP server\n273: - **WHEN** client sends POST/PUT/PATCH request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n274: - **THEN** the server SHALL parse the request body as JSON\n275: \n276: ### AR-004-051: Error response format\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** HTTP server returning an error\n279: - **WHEN** error occurs during request processing\n280: - **THEN** the response SHALL be a JSON object with `kind` = \"Status\", `apiVersion` = \"v1\", `status` = \"Failure\"\n281: - **AND** SHALL include `message`, `reason`, and `code` fields\n282: - **AND** SHALL follow Kubernetes API error format\n283: \n284: ---\n285: \n286: ## Scenario: Integration with client-go\n287: \n288: ### AR-004-060: Use RuntimeV1alpha1 Clientset\n289: \n290: - **GIVEN** a configured Kubernetes client\n291: - **WHEN** accessing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resources\n292: - **THEN** the server SHALL use the `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor from the Clientset\n293: - **AND** SHALL use typed clients for all CRUD operations\n294: \n295: ### AR-004-061: Use Informers for read operations\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory is configured\n298: - **WHEN** serving list requests\n299: - **THEN** the server SHOULD use the Informer cache for faster responses\n300: - **AND** SHALL fall back to direct API calls if cache is not ready\n301: \n302: ### AR-004-062: Use Listers for cached reads\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeLister is available\n305: - **WHEN** serving GET/List requests for AgentRuntime\n306: - **THEN** the server SHALL use the Lister for cached reads\n307: - **AND** SHALL return consistent data from the cache\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Scenario: ClusterRole & RBAC\n312: \n313: ### AR-004-070: Required RBAC permissions\n314: \n315: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager deployed with ServiceAccount\n316: - **WHEN** making API calls to Kubernetes\n317: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch AgentRuntime resources\n318: - **AND** SHALL have permissions to create, get, list, update, patch, delete, and watch CodeInterpreter resources\n319: - **AND** SHALL have permissions to list/watch pods and events in relevant namespaces\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ## References\n324: \n325: - client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n326: - AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n327: - CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n328: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 328 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (clientset, informers, listers)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775842540886,"end":1775842540908}}}}
