{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842611377,"sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","part":{"id":"prt_d787737f70018VqRmJQvcUYU6K","messageID":"msg_d787715d3001cyspJ2IjsyVNlK","sessionID":"ses_287898b9effe1VPnP95tbaHQ63","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_9df0e6cc576e48fcaf5022c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-005\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n\n### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource in namespace \"default\" with valid TargetPorts and PodTemplate\n- **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the AgentRuntime specification\n- **AND** SHALL create a Pod matching the PodTemplate specification\n- **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent AgentRuntime\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n\n### AR-005-002: Create Sandbox from CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource in namespace \"default\" with valid Template configuration\n- **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the CodeInterpreter template specification\n- **AND** SHALL create a Pod using the ContainerTemplateSpec\n- **AND** SHALL apply warm pool logic if WarmPoolSize > 0\n- **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n\n### AR-005-003: Sandbox creation with custom parameters\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource\n- **WHEN** a POST request includes custom override parameters in the request body\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the overrides to the sandbox specification\n- **AND** SHALL validate that override values meet validation constraints\n- **AND** SHALL merge overrides with the base template\n\n### AR-005-004: Sandbox creation validation failure\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with invalid PodTemplate (e.g., missing required container image)\n- **WHEN** a POST request attempts to create a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n- **AND** SHALL include validation error details in the response\n\n### AR-005-005: Sandbox creation for non-existent resource\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** a POST request targets a non-existent AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n\n### AR-005-010: Get Sandbox Status\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active sandboxes\n- **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return the current sandbox status including:\n  - Pod phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n  - Container states\n  - IP address if assigned\n  - Creation timestamp\n  - Parent resource reference (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n\n### AR-005-011: List Sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances running in a namespace\n- **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return a list of all sandboxes in the namespace\n- **AND** SHALL support labelSelector query parameter for filtering\n- **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata and status summary\n\n### AR-005-012: Delete Sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing sandbox instance\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate the sandbox Pod\n- **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n\n### AR-005-013: Delete Sandbox with force option\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully terminate the sandbox\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n\n### AR-005-014: Watch Sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances\n- **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?watch=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL stream sandbox events as NDJSON\n- **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as sandboxes change state\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Template Processing\n\n### AR-005-020: Process AgentRuntime PodTemplate\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a PodTemplate containing custom containers, volumes, and node selectors\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL merge the PodTemplate.Spec with default values\n- **AND** SHALL apply the specified NodeSelector, Affinity, and Tolerations\n- **AND** SHALL preserve InitContainers if specified\n\n### AR-005-021: Process CodeInterpreter ContainerTemplate\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a ContainerTemplate (image, command, args, env, resources)\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Pod with a single container from the template\n- **AND** SHALL apply resource requirements from the template\n- **AND** SHALL set the RuntimeClassName if specified\n\n### AR-005-022: Apply Security Context\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with SecurityContext configured\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL apply PodSecurityContext to the Pod\n- **AND** SHALL apply SecurityContext to each container\n- **AND** SHALL validate security context values against policy\n\n### AR-005-023: Inject Environment Variables\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with Env variables in the template\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL inject the specified environment variables\n- **AND** SHALL support both static values and references (e.g., from secrets, configmaps)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Pool Management\n\n### AR-005-030: Warm Pool Pre-provisioning\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize = 3\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is created or becomes ready\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL proactively create 3 sandbox Pods\n- **AND** SHALL mark them as warm/ready\n- **AND** SHALL maintain the warm pool size\n\n### AR-005-031: Warm Pool Scaling\n\n- **GIVEN** a warm pool with 3 ready sandboxes\n- **WHEN** a new sandbox request arrives and all warm sandboxes are in use\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL create an additional sandbox to handle the request\n- **AND** SHALL attempt to maintain the warm pool size\n\n### AR-005-032: Warm Pool Cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize reduced from 5 to 2\n- **WHEN** the pool size change is detected\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate excess warm sandboxes\n- **AND** SHALL gracefully drain unused sandboxes first\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Networking\n\n### AR-005-040: Expose Sandbox Ports\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts configured (port 8080, protocol HTTP)\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Service exposing the specified ports\n- **AND** SHALL set up appropriate network policies if configured\n- **AND** SHALL configure ingress routing based on PathPrefix\n\n### AR-005-041: Sandbox Ingress Configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts including PathPrefix \"/api\"\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL configure ingress rules for the specified path\n- **AND** SHALL ensure the path prefix is routed to the correct container port\n\n### AR-005-042: Network Policy Enforcement\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with network policy requirements\n- **WHEN** creating network resources\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL apply NetworkPolicy resources to restrict traffic\n- **AND** SHALL support both ingress and egress rules\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Scheduling\n\n### AR-005-050: Node Selection\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with NodeSelector configured (disktype=ssd, region=us-west)\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL schedule the Pod on a node matching the node selectors\n- **AND** SHALL handle scheduling failures gracefully\n\n### AR-005-051: Affinity and Anti-Affinity\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Affinity rules (podAntiAffinity, nodeAffinity)\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the affinity rules to Pod scheduling\n- **AND** SHALL respect both required and preferred affinity rules\n\n### AR-005-052: Resource Quota Enforcement\n\n- **GIVEN** a namespace with ResourceQuota limiting CPU, memory, or pod count\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox exceeds quota\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n- **AND** SHALL include quota violation details in the response\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Error Handling and Recovery\n\n### AR-005-060: Pod Creation Failure\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request\n- **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during Pod creation\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code (4xx or 5xx)\n- **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n- **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n\n### AR-005-061: Sandbox Status Sync\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod has crashed or been killed externally\n- **WHEN** querying sandbox status\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL detect the stale state\n- **AND** SHALL update the sandbox status to reflect the actual Pod state\n- **AND** SHALL emit events for status changes\n\n### AR-005-062: Graceful Shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** a running sandbox\n- **WHEN** the WorkloadManager receives shutdown signal\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL not accept new sandbox requests\n- **AND** SHALL wait for in-flight sandbox creations to complete\n- **AND** SHALL not terminate existing sandboxes (responsibility of controller)\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n- Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n- AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [33:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [40:9] invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter) is not an interface\nERROR [66:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [73:9] invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter) is not an interface\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP err